Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveThomas Markle, the father of the Duchess of Sussex, Meghan Markle has vowed to testify against her and her husband, Prince Harry in court.
He said this on Sunday as he started his YouTube channel.
Meghan’s half-sister, Samantha had brought a court case against her for allegedly lying against her and their family in their exclusive interview with Oprah Winfrey, reports Daily Mail.
ALSO READ: Meghan Markle’s sister sues over Oprah Winfrey interview
Mr Markle said he believed his eldest daughter should win her case and revealed he would be willing to give evidence on her behalf.
He said, “I would be more than happy to. I’ve been trying for almost four years to get to see my daughter and her ginger husband in a courtroom face-to-face. I’d be thrilled to defend my oldest daughter.”
